```turtle
# Wikipedia Knowledge Extraction Module

@prefix : <http://ex.com/mv#> .
@prefix rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#> .
@prefix rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#> .
@prefix xsd: <http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema#> .

# Classes
:WikipediaArticle rdf:type owl:Class . 📚

# Properties
:hasTitle rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
          rdfs:domain :WikipediaArticle ;
          rdfs:range xsd:string . 🏷️

:hasContent rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
            rdfs:domain :WikipediaArticle ;
            rdfs:range xsd:string . 📝

# Examples
# Wikipedia article about the metaverse
#
metaverseArticle rdf:type WikipediaArticle ;
                 hasTitle "Metaverse" ;
                 hasContent "The metaverse is a virtual reality space..." . 🎮📚🏷️📝

# Wikipedia article about avatars
#
avatarsArticle rdf:type WikipediaArticle ;
               hasTitle "Avatars" ;
               hasContent "An avatar is a graphical representation..." . 👤📚🏷️📝

# Linking articles to ontology instances
#
:Metaverse rdfs:seeAlso metaverseArticle . 🎮🔗📚
:Avatar rdfs:seeAlso avatarsArticle . 👤🔗📚
```

This Wikipedia Knowledge Extraction Module allows you to link Wikipedia articles to ontology instances. It defines a class `WikipediaArticle` and properties `hasTitle` and `hasContent` to associate titles and content with articles. You can use the `rdfs:seeAlso` property to link ontology classes to Wikipedia articles for reference.

